### **FPIC: Success vs Failure — Side-by-Side Comparison (Plain English)**

| **Factor** | **SUCCESS (Works)** | **FAILURE (Breaks)** |
|-----------|---------------------|----------------------|
| **Timing** | **Early** — Ask **before** any plans or digging | **Late** — Ask *after* machines arrive |
| **Information** | **Full truth** — All risks, benefits, and long-term effects explained | **Half-truths** — Hide pollution, displacement, or costs |
| **Pressure** | **Free choice** — No threats, bribes, or force | **Forced** — Police, money, or “sign or lose” |
| **Consent** | **Real YES** — Community votes openly and agrees | **Ignored NO** — They say NO, but project goes anyway |
| **Leadership** | **Community-led** — Elders and members run meetings | **Top-down** — Government or company controls talks |
| **Benefits** | **Fair share** — Jobs, money, or land rights go to locals | **Empty promises** — “Jobs coming” but none appear |
| **Follow-Up** | **Kept promises** — Regular checks, payments on time | **Broken trust** — Agreements ignored after start |
| **Outcome** | **Win-Win** — Project runs, people gain, no protests | **Lose-Lose** — Delays, lawsuits, damage, shame |

---

### **Real Examples**

| **Success** | **Failure** |
|------------|-------------|
| **Innu + Voisey Bay Mine** (Canada) | **Dakota Access Pipeline** (USA) |
| Asked 2 years early<br>Shared profits<br>Innu co-own 7% | Started without asking<br>Used dogs on protesters<br>Ignored NO |
| **Result**: $2B in benefits, 20+ years of peace | **Result**: $1B+ in delays, global outrage |

| **Success** | **Failure** |
|------------|-------------|
| **Baram Dam Canceled** (Malaysia) | **Belo Monte Dam** (Brazil) |
| Tribes said NO → government stopped | Tribes said NO → dam built anyway |
| **Result**: Forests saved | **Result**: 20,000 homeless, UN condemned |

